{
  "texts": [
    "In a way, this goes along with Foucault's notion on authorship.",
    "For him, the concept of the author serves as a function of discourse rather than as a fixed and genuine identity of a given individual.",
    "This \"author function\" is not universal or constant across all texts or periods.",
    "Rather, it varies depending on the context, such as in scientific versus literary texts.",
    "Foucault's critique extends to how society and legal systems privilege the author as a source of creativity and originality, which in turn affects the classification, interpretation, and valuation of texts."
  ]
}